# Ensures consistent line endings, diff rules, and file handling
# across Windows, macOS, and Linux environments.
# ==========================================================

# === Line Endings ===
# Normalize all text files to LF in the repo, CRLF on Windows
* text=auto eol=lf
*.bat text eol=crlf
*.cmd text eol=crlf
*.ps1 text eol=crlf

# === Source Code ===
*.py text diff=python
*.qss text
*.iss text
*.json text
*.txt text
*.md text
*.yml text
*.yaml text

# === OS / Binary / Media Files ===
*.ico binary
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.bmp binary
*.wav binary
*.mp3 binary
*.flac binary
*.exe binary
*.dll binary

# === Project-Specific ===
*.spec text
*.log text
*.cfg text

# === Windows Explorer Artifacts (Prevent Merge Conflicts) ===
Thumbs.db binary
ehthumbs.db binary
Icon? binary
desktop.ini binary

# ==========================================================
# âœ… RESULT:
#   - All Python & text files use LF in repo
#   - Windows batch and PowerShell scripts stay CRLF
#   - Images, music, and binaries are stored exactly as-is
# ==========================================================
